## ⚡ Quick Revision Cheatsheet

```
OOP
├── class MyClass:              → define a class
├── def __init__(self, ...):    → constructor
├── self.attr = value           → instance variable
├── @property                   → getter as attribute
├── @staticmethod               → utility, no self/cls
├── @classmethod                → access class, no self
└── super().__init__(...)       → call parent constructor

FUNCTIONS
├── def func(*args, **kwargs):  → flexible signature
├── lambda x: expression        → anonymous one-liner
├── map(fn, iterable)           → apply fn to all
├── filter(fn, iterable)        → keep where fn is True
├── reduce(fn, iterable)        → collapse to one value
└── @decorator                  → wrap a function

LIST COMPREHENSIONS
├── [expr for x in iterable]              → basic
├── [expr for x in iterable if cond]      → filtered
├── [expr if cond else other for x in it] → ternary
├── [x for row in matrix for x in row]    → flatten
├── {k: v for k, v in items}              → dict comp
├── {x for x in iterable}                 → set comp
└── (x for x in iterable)                 → generator
```

